

### Cole slaw

* 1 medium cabbage, cored and sliced or shredded finely
* 1 T grated sweet onion
* 1 grated carrot
* 1 C mayo
* 1/4 C white vinegar
* 1 T sugar
* salt and pepper

* Combine ingredients
* serve as soon as possible


### Sweet Home Cafe

* 1 head cabbage ~2.5lb; core and ribs removed; leaves thinly sliced
* 1 C carrot
* 1/2 cup sweet onion
* 1/4 cup cider vinegar
* 1/4 cup sugar
* 1/2 t celery salt
* 1/4 t kosher salt
* 1 C mayo
* 1/3 cup sweet pickle relish
* 1.5 t Creole mustard (Zatarain's) or Dijon
* 2 dashes Tabasco
* pepper to taste

* combine cabbage, carrot, onion in large bowl
* combine vinegar, sugar, celery salt, kosher salt; whisk until dissolved
* add mayo, relish, mustard, tabasco, pepper; whisk until blended
* fold mayo mixture into cabbage with rubber spatula
* refrigerate for a minimum of 3 hours before serving
* keeps for 1 day




### Blueberry cole slaw
### Pyles p. 192


* ~2 lbs cabbage
* 1 cup julienned celery
* 1 cup thinly sliced red onion
* 2 cups mayo
* 1/4 cup red wine vinegar
* 1/3 cup ancho chile puree
* salt
* 1 cup fresh blueberries
* 1 cup roasted peanuts

* combine vegetables in mixing bowl
* different bowl: combine mayo, vinegar, chile puree, salt
* fold mayo into vegetables
* add 3/4 cup blueberries, peanuts to slaw

